1
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:54,480
Treat my father.

2
00:02:55,440 --> 00:02:57,120
You know who my father is, right?

3
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:00,600
Come work for me.

4
00:03:02,840 --> 00:03:04,240
We love each other.

5
00:03:04,880 --> 00:03:05,760
One day, she'll understand.

6
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:10,360
That's none of your business.

7
00:03:10,440 --> 00:03:13,000
How is it not? He's not just your dad.

8
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:14,160
Prapai.

9
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:15,680
You have a girlfriend,

10
00:03:16,320 --> 00:03:18,720
a sister. How can you do this to me?

11
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:21,880
We've searched everything.
There's nothing.

12
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:23,240
It's not in the laptop either.

13
00:03:24,720 --> 00:03:26,400
Raka, run!

14
00:03:26,480 --> 00:03:28,160
Run!

15
00:03:31,120 --> 00:03:32,000
Mom…

16
00:03:42,640 --> 00:03:44,080
Come here!

17
00:03:45,440 --> 00:03:46,960
Uncle.

18
00:03:50,360 --> 00:03:51,880
Go!

19
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:56,000
Don't hurt me, please.

20
00:03:56,080 --> 00:03:58,440
Quiet! Don't scream!

21
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:01,600
Be quiet. Stay right there.

22
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:09,240
It's me.

23
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:14,120
You're trying to buy me off again?

24
00:04:15,320 --> 00:04:18,600
How much this time?
How much is your daughter worth?

25
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:21,320
Fine.

26
00:04:22,920 --> 00:04:24,520
Fifty million then.

27
00:04:27,560 --> 00:04:28,920
Fifty million?

28
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:30,880
Where am I supposed to get that?

29
00:04:30,960 --> 00:04:33,760
Fifty million is nothing to you!

30
00:04:33,840 --> 00:04:35,640
Please calm down.

31
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:38,920
No one carries that much cash.

32
00:04:39,960 --> 00:04:41,480
How about this?

33
00:04:42,120 --> 00:04:43,520
Reduce the amount,

34
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:46,080
and we'll arrange it immediately.

35
00:04:47,240 --> 00:04:49,200
What about 20 million?

36
00:04:50,240 --> 00:04:51,840
Twenty million?

37
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:55,440
Your daughter's life
is worth only 20 million to you?

38
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:04,280
Talk to your father!

39
00:05:07,120 --> 00:05:09,440
Dad, I'm scared.

40
00:05:11,280 --> 00:05:13,360
<i>Dad, I'm scared.</i>

41
00:05:13,440 --> 00:05:14,560
Don't hurt my daughter.

42
00:05:15,160 --> 00:05:16,200
- Come here.
- Uncle.

43
00:05:16,280 --> 00:05:18,080
Uncle…

44
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:20,280
Come here! Twenty million? Fine.

45
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:22,760
Then you'll only get her hand.

46
00:05:23,880 --> 00:05:26,760
Uncle! Uncle!

47
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:40,280
Fahsai? Are you okay?

48
00:05:45,880 --> 00:05:49,840
Did you hear her cry?
Your daughter's still alive.

49
00:05:50,480 --> 00:05:53,680
Fine. I'll bring the money.

50
00:05:54,240 --> 00:05:57,200
Fahsai, are you alright?

51
00:06:33,520 --> 00:06:34,480
Uncle…

52
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:38,520
Please don't do this.

53
00:06:39,040 --> 00:06:41,040
I know you don't hate me.

54
00:06:43,880 --> 00:06:46,040
You've been driving me to school
since I was a child.

55
00:06:47,880 --> 00:06:50,680
You even bought me snacks.

56
00:06:51,680 --> 00:06:53,280
If you want money,

57
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:55,560
I'll transfer it.
I'll give you everything I have.

58
00:06:55,640 --> 00:06:57,400
I'll give you every single baht.

59
00:06:58,160 --> 00:06:59,840
Just tell me how much you want.

60
00:07:02,640 --> 00:07:04,640
I don't want anyone's money!

61
00:07:07,480 --> 00:07:09,120
I don't care about that damn money!

62
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:15,320
I just want to teach him
that money isn't everything.

63
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:18,720
Some things can't be replaced by money.

64
00:07:18,800 --> 00:07:19,960
Do you understand?

65
00:07:30,080 --> 00:07:31,320
My child…

66
00:07:39,520 --> 00:07:40,480
Here.

67
00:07:41,440 --> 00:07:44,480
This is compensation. Take it.

68
00:07:54,560 --> 00:07:56,360
Money can't replace it.

69
00:07:57,880 --> 00:07:59,080
You don't understand.

70
00:07:59,960 --> 00:08:01,720
Money can't replace it!

71
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:03,320
Money can't replace it!

72
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:06,280
I just want to see him
bring the cash here himself!

73
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:09,120
And he has to suffer like I did!

74
00:08:09,200 --> 00:08:10,480
And he has to suffer like I did!

75
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:15,360
And he has to suffer like I did!

76
00:08:28,120 --> 00:08:29,680
That's enough. Stop!

77
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:49,960
‪Hey! Hey!

78
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:57,920
Stop!

79
00:08:58,000 --> 00:09:00,000
- This way.
- Hey! Stop!

80
00:09:05,040 --> 00:09:06,160
Stop right there!

81
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:08,520
Stop!

82
00:09:20,680 --> 00:09:21,880
Keep going.

83
00:09:22,880 --> 00:09:24,520
I said stop!

84
00:09:26,280 --> 00:09:27,240
Hey.

85
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:40,360
Get up.

86
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:43,000
Hurry!

87
00:09:46,520 --> 00:09:47,600
Hey.

88
00:10:08,520 --> 00:10:10,200
Don't run!

89
00:11:02,680 --> 00:11:03,920
Wait here.

90
00:11:33,920 --> 00:11:35,880
It's fine. I can walk.

91
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:36,640
Sit down and rest first.

92
00:12:47,560 --> 00:12:48,440
What are you doing?

93
00:12:51,440 --> 00:12:54,320
Your bleeding hasn't stopped.
I'm going to stop it for you.

94
00:12:54,400 --> 00:12:55,720
But your arm…

95
00:12:55,800 --> 00:12:56,920
It's fine.

96
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:02,760
Just hang in there.

97
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:30,200
Don't be scared.

98
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:33,400
We'll get out of here.

99
00:14:37,920 --> 00:14:38,960
Trust me.

100
00:14:51,120 --> 00:14:52,760
Does it hurt? Is it too tight?

101
00:19:07,120 --> 00:19:07,960
Hey.

102
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:11,040
Hey.

103
00:19:23,520 --> 00:19:24,800
Let's go borrow her phone.

104
00:19:40,240 --> 00:19:41,440
I'll go.

105
00:19:46,280 --> 00:19:47,720
Excuse me.

106
00:19:48,280 --> 00:19:50,160
May I borrow your phone, please?

107
00:20:18,040 --> 00:20:21,360
<i>A horrifying incident took place</i>
<i>at house number 13/66.</i>

108
00:20:21,440 --> 00:20:24,880
<i>Mrs. Kulvipa Jaiaree, Miss Peekul Jaiaree,</i>

109
00:20:24,960 --> 00:20:27,360
<i>and their neighbor,</i>
<i>Mr. Prakat Phitakhacha,</i>

110
00:20:27,440 --> 00:20:29,000
<i>were brutally murdered.</i>

111
00:20:29,080 --> 00:20:29,920
KULVIPA JAIAREE, PEEKUL JAIAREE
PRAKAT PHITAKKHACHA

112
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:32,000
<i>The bodies were found</i>
<i>with more than ten stab wounds,</i>

113
00:20:32,080 --> 00:20:33,600
<i>as well as gunshot wounds.</i>

114
00:20:34,680 --> 00:20:37,720
<i>Police believe the perpetrator</i>
<i>is Mr. Peeraka Jaiaree,</i>

115
00:20:37,800 --> 00:20:39,160
<i>the son of the deceased,</i>

116
00:20:39,240 --> 00:20:42,040
<i>an intern doctor</i>
<i>at a well-known public hospital.</i>

117
00:20:42,120 --> 00:20:45,120
<i>The preliminary assumption is that he may</i>
<i>have committed it under severe stress.</i>

118
00:20:45,760 --> 00:20:49,360
<i>Bullets and a gun holster</i>
<i>were found in the suspect's bedroom,</i>

119
00:20:49,440 --> 00:20:51,480
<i>matching the murder weapon.</i>

120
00:20:51,560 --> 00:20:52,800
<i>It's believed</i>
<i>that the neighbor, Mr. Prakat,</i>

121
00:20:52,880 --> 00:20:55,840
<i>discovered the incident</i>
<i>and was therefore murdered as well.</i>

122
00:20:56,640 --> 00:20:58,360
- Fahsai.
- Dad.

123
00:21:05,720 --> 00:21:08,640
You're okay now.

124
00:21:08,720 --> 00:21:11,440
You're safe now.

125
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:15,040
Somkid has already been arrested.
You're safe now.

126
00:21:20,080 --> 00:21:23,280
What happened to your arm?

127
00:21:25,400 --> 00:21:26,800
I'm fine.

128
00:21:26,880 --> 00:21:29,160
Someone helped me. He's over there--

129
00:21:31,160 --> 00:21:32,080
Oh?

130
00:21:33,440 --> 00:21:35,520
- Just a second.
- Fahsai.

131
00:21:48,320 --> 00:21:51,560
<i>Police are currently searching</i>
<i>for Mr. Peeraka Jaiaree,</i>

132
00:21:51,640 --> 00:21:54,440
<i>the prime suspect</i>
<i>in the murder of his own family.</i>

133
00:21:54,520 --> 00:21:58,680
<i>Anyone who sees him or has any information</i>
<i>is urged to contact authorities.</i>

134
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:02,120
That can't be true…

135
00:22:03,640 --> 00:22:04,840
What is it?

136
00:22:08,840 --> 00:22:09,840
Nothing, Dad.

137
00:22:12,680 --> 00:22:15,480
Come on. Let's go home.
We need to get you to a doctor.

138
00:22:26,080 --> 00:22:27,680
Be careful. Watch your step.

139
00:22:44,080 --> 00:22:45,280
May.

140
00:22:47,240 --> 00:22:48,120
It's me.

141
00:22:51,880 --> 00:22:54,000
I was afraid someone might hear.

142
00:22:55,960 --> 00:22:58,640
You saw the news, right?

143
00:23:02,240 --> 00:23:04,000
I didn't do it.

144
00:23:04,520 --> 00:23:06,280
I don't know why the news is saying that.

145
00:23:07,480 --> 00:23:09,880
But why did I suddenly become a murderer?

146
00:23:13,320 --> 00:23:16,240
I believe you. I know you didn't do it.

147
00:23:16,840 --> 00:23:18,920
You would never do something like that.

148
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:20,360
It has to be them.

149
00:23:21,720 --> 00:23:23,360
It has to be those people.

150
00:23:25,960 --> 00:23:26,840
They…

151
00:23:36,640 --> 00:23:39,400
They killed Mom and Kul…

152
00:23:41,880 --> 00:23:43,480
and then blamed it on me.

153
00:23:45,520 --> 00:23:48,080
Calm down first, Raka. Calm down.

154
00:23:49,520 --> 00:23:50,360
I…

155
00:23:51,160 --> 00:23:52,720
I don't know what to do anymore.

156
00:23:53,840 --> 00:23:57,000
With the news like this,
everyone will think

157
00:23:58,360 --> 00:24:00,680
I'm a murderer who killed my own family.

158
00:24:04,720 --> 00:24:05,920
Don't be scared.

159
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:07,560
Don't be scared.

160
00:24:08,200 --> 00:24:11,320
My dad promised he'd help you.

161
00:24:14,040 --> 00:24:14,880
But…

162
00:24:15,560 --> 00:24:19,000
Uncle Singha is a police officer.
Will he really help me?

163
00:24:20,360 --> 00:24:23,760
Of course. We're like family.

164
00:24:23,840 --> 00:24:25,880
My dad is really worried about you.

165
00:24:28,520 --> 00:24:29,600
Thank you.

166
00:24:52,840 --> 00:24:57,480
THE SCAPEGOAT SETUP HAS BEGUN
POLICE ARE ON THE WAY

167
00:25:09,880 --> 00:25:11,520
Raka. Raka.

168
00:25:11,600 --> 00:25:13,000
Raka, don't run.

169
00:25:13,080 --> 00:25:15,320
Raka, don't run.

170
00:25:15,400 --> 00:25:17,160
Please. Just turn yourself in.

171
00:25:17,240 --> 00:25:18,640
You called the police?

172
00:25:19,560 --> 00:25:20,400
Why?

173
00:25:21,400 --> 00:25:23,120
I told you I didn't do it.

174
00:25:23,920 --> 00:25:26,680
Whether you did or not,
just surrender and fight the case.

175
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:29,400
You can't run.

176
00:25:29,480 --> 00:25:31,360
You can't fight them.

177
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:32,880
Them?

178
00:25:34,520 --> 00:25:35,440
Why?

179
00:25:36,640 --> 00:25:40,240
You know who they are, don't you?
You know, right?

180
00:25:40,320 --> 00:25:44,240
Raka, please.
If you don't want to die, don't run.

181
00:25:44,320 --> 00:25:46,480
Please, Raka. Don't run.

182
00:25:47,440 --> 00:25:49,280
Mr. Peeraka Jaiaree.

183
00:25:50,200 --> 00:25:52,440
The area is surrounded.

184
00:25:52,520 --> 00:25:55,320
Drop your weapon, release the hostage,

185
00:25:56,000 --> 00:25:57,440
and surrender immediately.

186
00:25:58,280 --> 00:25:59,640
What is he talking about?

187
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:03,880
I don't have a gun.

188
00:26:03,960 --> 00:26:06,120
And since when are you my hostage?

189
00:26:10,560 --> 00:26:12,080
Why are you doing this to me?

190
00:26:13,520 --> 00:26:15,080
We're a couple, aren't we?

191
00:26:15,160 --> 00:26:18,240
We promised we'd face
everything together, didn't we?

192
00:26:21,360 --> 00:26:23,040
Raka.

193
00:26:23,120 --> 00:26:25,840
- Raka, please don't run.
- Stay away from me.

194
00:26:25,920 --> 00:26:27,920
Raka!

195
00:26:28,520 --> 00:26:29,560
Go.

196
00:26:44,360 --> 00:26:47,040
We need backup now.

197
00:28:27,960 --> 00:28:29,000
Help…

198
00:29:42,360 --> 00:29:43,880
It's a shame

199
00:29:43,960 --> 00:29:45,880
Raka wouldn't turn himself in.

200
00:29:47,160 --> 00:29:50,320
Otherwise, he probably wouldn't have
run off and gotten into that accident.

201
00:29:55,440 --> 00:29:57,080
I trusted you.

202
00:29:58,200 --> 00:29:59,960
I did what you told me to do.

203
00:30:01,200 --> 00:30:02,400
But in the end…

204
00:30:04,520 --> 00:30:07,280
it feels like I'm the one who killed Raka.

205
00:30:10,760 --> 00:30:12,000
Don't say that.

206
00:30:13,320 --> 00:30:15,720
What happened wasn't because of you.

207
00:30:18,040 --> 00:30:20,240
Those people created
the problem themselves.

208
00:30:21,040 --> 00:30:22,480
What choice did we have?

209
00:30:26,520 --> 00:30:28,200
If Raka loved you,

210
00:30:29,120 --> 00:30:30,640
he'd understand.

211
00:30:31,320 --> 00:30:34,880
Your boyfriend is gone,
but you're still here.

212
00:30:36,160 --> 00:30:37,880
The living have to keep going.

213
00:30:39,280 --> 00:30:40,840
Forget this

214
00:30:42,240 --> 00:30:43,480
and start over.

215
00:30:49,640 --> 00:30:51,600
Peeraka had been saying lately

216
00:30:51,680 --> 00:30:53,680
that he was under a lot of stress.

217
00:30:55,320 --> 00:30:57,040
Being an intern is hard,

218
00:30:57,120 --> 00:31:01,120
and he also had
some problems with his sister.

219
00:31:01,800 --> 00:31:05,400
And when did he start
telling you about these problems?

220
00:31:07,200 --> 00:31:10,480
Only recently.

221
00:31:10,560 --> 00:31:14,400
Did he ever say
he wanted to hurt his family?

222
00:31:17,880 --> 00:31:19,960
Please don't make me talk about that.

223
00:31:20,800 --> 00:31:22,680
He's gone now.

224
00:31:24,280 --> 00:31:27,600
At the time, I never thought
he was under that much stress.

225
00:31:37,840 --> 00:31:39,000
Lieutenant?

226
00:31:41,640 --> 00:31:42,840
Lieutenant?

227
00:31:43,960 --> 00:31:44,800
Lieutenant?

228
00:31:47,640 --> 00:31:49,000
Oh?

229
00:31:49,640 --> 00:31:50,920
It's not locked.

230
00:31:51,000 --> 00:31:52,280
Kaitod.

231
00:31:54,360 --> 00:31:57,000
Kaitod. Kaitod.

232
00:31:57,920 --> 00:31:59,000
Where's your dad?

233
00:32:01,920 --> 00:32:04,560
Where'd your dad go?

234
00:32:04,640 --> 00:32:06,600
Not answering?

235
00:32:07,600 --> 00:32:08,680
What a mess.

236
00:32:14,760 --> 00:32:17,120
Hey? Lieutenant!

237
00:32:22,800 --> 00:32:25,600
Lieutenant, please eat something.

238
00:32:31,920 --> 00:32:33,960
If you want to cry,
then cry your heart out.

239
00:32:35,480 --> 00:32:37,880
A real policeman should know how to cry.

240
00:32:39,200 --> 00:32:41,920
Lieutenant, it's actually good.

241
00:32:42,000 --> 00:32:43,240
It's trendy now.

242
00:32:43,320 --> 00:32:46,440
A man crying gives him depth. Go ahead.

243
00:32:46,520 --> 00:32:48,920
Cry your eyes out.

244
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:49,840
Enough.

245
00:32:58,480 --> 00:32:59,520
You know,

246
00:33:02,120 --> 00:33:03,600
ever since I became a cop,

247
00:33:05,080 --> 00:33:06,640
I always thought…

248
00:33:08,320 --> 00:33:10,520
I'd be the one to leave her first
because of this job.

249
00:33:16,120 --> 00:33:19,680
What kind of sick joke is this…

250
00:33:20,520 --> 00:33:22,920
that she had to go first?

251
00:33:31,560 --> 00:33:34,640
Kaitod. Kaitod.

252
00:33:47,520 --> 00:33:51,240
I only raised him because of her.

253
00:33:53,960 --> 00:33:56,520
I named him after her favorite food.

254
00:34:02,600 --> 00:34:03,760
And now she's gone

255
00:34:03,840 --> 00:34:06,280
because her own brother
slaughtered the whole family?

256
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:10,920
Lieutenant,

257
00:34:11,760 --> 00:34:13,520
you still don't believe it?

258
00:34:15,560 --> 00:34:18,159
Even though those siblings
fought all the time,

259
00:34:18,760 --> 00:34:21,760
I never thought Peeraka
was capable of murder.

260
00:34:24,800 --> 00:34:27,560
But who the hell knows?

261
00:34:28,800 --> 00:34:30,920
Some killers who butcher bodies

262
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:32,920
don't even look like killers.

263
00:34:36,040 --> 00:34:37,639
And when I wanted to investigate,

264
00:34:38,280 --> 00:34:40,480
Captain Singha said
I was too close to the case

265
00:34:40,560 --> 00:34:42,480
and might be biased.

266
00:34:42,560 --> 00:34:45,120
Then suddenly, the case was closed.

267
00:34:45,840 --> 00:34:49,239
Lieutenant, the dead are already dead.

268
00:34:49,320 --> 00:34:52,159
Sergeant,

269
00:34:54,120 --> 00:34:56,159
that doesn't make wrong right.

270
00:34:58,120 --> 00:35:02,000
Lieutenant, this case is closed.

271
00:35:03,040 --> 00:35:04,840
All the evidence

272
00:35:04,920 --> 00:35:08,040
points to your girlfriend's brother.

273
00:35:08,120 --> 00:35:09,840
Even his own girlfriend gave an interview.

274
00:35:15,440 --> 00:35:16,320
Lieutenant,

275
00:35:16,400 --> 00:35:17,640
I think

276
00:35:18,240 --> 00:35:21,360
if you keep going in circles like this
and can't move on,

277
00:35:21,440 --> 00:35:23,520
then you're basically another dead man.

278
00:35:29,200 --> 00:35:30,720
Think about it.

279
00:35:31,840 --> 00:35:35,880
Would a fighter like Ms. Peekul
want to see you like this?

280
00:35:52,800 --> 00:35:56,600
Win, why did you ask me to meet you here?

281
00:36:01,400 --> 00:36:03,640
- Isn't he cute?
- He's so cute.

282
00:36:05,920 --> 00:36:09,280
Hi there. You're adorable.

283
00:36:09,360 --> 00:36:10,840
Whose dog is this?

284
00:36:10,920 --> 00:36:12,280
Yours.

285
00:36:12,360 --> 00:36:13,560
Huh?

286
00:36:14,080 --> 00:36:16,520
Hello. My name is Kaitod.

287
00:36:17,360 --> 00:36:20,160
You've been refusing to get a dog,
no matter how much I asked.

288
00:36:20,240 --> 00:36:22,000
What made you change your mind today?

289
00:36:22,080 --> 00:36:24,560
Well…

290
00:36:27,560 --> 00:36:28,840
Kaitod!

291
00:36:35,760 --> 00:36:36,880
Win!

292
00:36:47,600 --> 00:36:50,320
You could've just dodged him.
The path is wide enough.

293
00:36:57,120 --> 00:36:58,280
Kaitod!

294
00:36:58,840 --> 00:37:00,000
Hey.

295
00:37:01,080 --> 00:37:02,240
Kaitod!

296
00:37:02,760 --> 00:37:03,600
Win!

297
00:37:07,440 --> 00:37:08,560
- Win!
- Kaitod!

298
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:11,360
- Win!
- Kaitod!

299
00:37:32,080 --> 00:37:33,840
Kaitod, come here.

300
00:37:34,360 --> 00:37:35,920
Come here.

301
00:37:40,040 --> 00:37:41,240
Kaitod.

302
00:37:44,480 --> 00:37:45,480
I'm sorry.

303
00:37:46,240 --> 00:37:47,400
Alright?

304
00:37:48,400 --> 00:37:51,040
Oh. Here, take this.

305
00:37:52,160 --> 00:37:53,800
Go buy another one, okay?

306
00:37:53,880 --> 00:37:56,880
Don't cry. I'm sorry. Go buy a new one.

307
00:38:02,600 --> 00:38:05,160
- Gosh, I thought I lost it.
- That's a diamond ring?

308
00:38:05,240 --> 00:38:06,120
Kul.

309
00:38:09,000 --> 00:38:09,840
That's why.

310
00:38:09,920 --> 00:38:13,960
No wonder you ran faster
than when chasing suspects.

311
00:38:14,040 --> 00:38:15,400
It's that expensive.

312
00:38:15,480 --> 00:38:17,680
No, it's not like that.

313
00:38:17,760 --> 00:38:21,480
I run like this when chasing suspects too.

314
00:38:21,560 --> 00:38:22,680
Whoa.

315
00:38:22,760 --> 00:38:26,120
Kaitod, you're named "Fried Chicken",
but you like grilled pork?

316
00:38:26,200 --> 00:38:29,840
See? The surprise is ruined.
Totally ruined.

317
00:38:30,440 --> 00:38:33,120
You're this clumsy.
Should I really marry you?

318
00:38:41,280 --> 00:38:44,640
But that's exactly
why I love you so much.

319
00:38:45,720 --> 00:38:46,560
Really?

320
00:38:47,480 --> 00:38:48,480
So…

321
00:38:50,520 --> 00:38:51,880
you'll marry me?

322
00:38:52,720 --> 00:38:54,360
Do you even have to ask?

323
00:38:55,720 --> 00:38:57,920
Yes! Yes! Yes!

324
00:38:58,000 --> 00:39:00,360
I'm so happy!

325
00:39:08,880 --> 00:39:10,680
MS. PEEKUL

326
00:39:14,920 --> 00:39:16,400
Kul, you can hear me, right?

327
00:39:19,560 --> 00:39:21,200
I'm going back to work now.

328
00:39:23,560 --> 00:39:25,200
I'll go back to being the person…

329
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:29,160
the one you loved.

330
00:39:31,680 --> 00:39:33,760
I'll make myself useful again.

331
00:39:36,920 --> 00:39:38,280
Cheer me on, okay?

332
00:39:40,560 --> 00:39:41,960
Help me keep going.

333
00:39:45,240 --> 00:39:46,840
Even without you.

334
00:40:07,160 --> 00:40:10,960
SIX YEARS LATER

335
00:40:12,320 --> 00:40:14,000
For the rest of my life,

336
00:40:15,560 --> 00:40:17,960
I will never be able to love anyone again.

337
00:40:20,360 --> 00:40:21,920
Even if I have to live alone,

338
00:40:23,520 --> 00:40:24,520
without a home,

339
00:40:26,120 --> 00:40:27,640
without wealth,

340
00:40:28,800 --> 00:40:30,320
without anything at all,

341
00:40:30,400 --> 00:40:32,600
I will still…

342
00:40:33,920 --> 00:40:35,680
love only you.

343
00:41:09,480 --> 00:41:10,960
Only flowers?

344
00:41:11,040 --> 00:41:13,840
Didn't Mr. Mahasamut come, Ms. Maysa?

345
00:41:13,920 --> 00:41:14,760
SAWAI SUTTHIPITAK

346
00:41:14,840 --> 00:41:16,760
Yeah.

347
00:41:16,840 --> 00:41:19,200
I told him not to.

348
00:41:19,280 --> 00:41:21,560
He has an important meeting.

349
00:41:21,640 --> 00:41:24,640
National matters come first.

350
00:41:24,720 --> 00:41:26,120
Just let him work.

351
00:41:26,200 --> 00:41:28,760
Wow.

352
00:41:28,840 --> 00:41:32,160
You're such a beautiful
and generous girlfriend.

353
00:41:32,240 --> 00:41:34,240
Mr. Mahasamut is very lucky.

354
00:41:34,320 --> 00:41:36,920
- Right?
- Yeah.

355
00:41:37,000 --> 00:41:38,800
Let's take some photos.

356
00:41:38,880 --> 00:41:39,720
Of course.

357
00:41:39,800 --> 00:41:41,960
- This way, please.
- This way too.

358
00:41:42,040 --> 00:41:44,440
- With the flowers too.
- This camera, please.

359
00:41:44,520 --> 00:41:46,000
This way, please.

360
00:41:46,080 --> 00:41:47,640
- This way, please.
- So beautiful.

361
00:42:30,560 --> 00:42:31,720
May.

362
00:42:33,640 --> 00:42:34,880
You didn't even try.

363
00:42:34,960 --> 00:42:36,160
You don't want it?

364
00:42:51,200 --> 00:42:52,640
You really pulled it off.

365
00:42:58,520 --> 00:42:59,560
Impossible.

366
00:43:05,960 --> 00:43:07,320
Excuse me. Wait.

367
00:43:08,400 --> 00:43:10,600
Please wait.

368
00:43:12,280 --> 00:43:13,360
Hey.

369
00:43:15,040 --> 00:43:18,280
Hey. Hey.

370
00:43:36,080 --> 00:43:36,920
Are you okay?

371
00:43:38,160 --> 00:43:39,400
Are you hurt?

372
00:43:42,720 --> 00:43:43,600
You…

373
00:43:50,000 --> 00:43:51,760
You look like…

374
00:43:51,840 --> 00:43:53,400
Like who?

375
00:44:01,760 --> 00:44:02,680
Your shoe came off.

376
00:44:10,360 --> 00:44:11,680
Thank you.

377
00:44:14,600 --> 00:44:16,040
Do you like them?

378
00:44:20,120 --> 00:44:22,200
Do you know what white lilies mean?

379
00:44:26,160 --> 00:44:27,120
I think…

380
00:44:29,720 --> 00:44:31,040
purity, maybe.

381
00:44:33,400 --> 00:44:36,880
That's one meaning. But there's another.

382
00:44:38,440 --> 00:44:39,920
Devotion.

383
00:44:44,640 --> 00:44:46,800
If someone once devoted themselves to you,

384
00:44:47,640 --> 00:44:49,600
you should have taken better care of them.

385
00:44:57,440 --> 00:44:58,520
Thank you for helping her.

386
00:45:01,800 --> 00:45:03,840
May has another appointment.

387
00:45:17,960 --> 00:45:19,400
Is there something on my face?

388
00:45:21,360 --> 00:45:22,320
No.

389
00:45:25,440 --> 00:45:28,760
You just look like someone I used to know.

390
00:45:32,080 --> 00:45:35,640
But only similar.
Definitely not the same person.

391
00:45:35,720 --> 00:45:37,120
That's a relief.

392
00:45:37,880 --> 00:45:39,280
I wouldn't want to look like anyone,

393
00:45:41,800 --> 00:45:43,560
especially someone useless.

394
00:45:45,680 --> 00:45:46,880
He's better than you.

395
00:45:46,960 --> 00:45:49,240
Do you even know me to say that?

396
00:45:58,280 --> 00:46:00,840
I'd like to invite you for coffee.

397
00:46:00,920 --> 00:46:02,880
We could talk more about your performance.

398
00:46:14,480 --> 00:46:16,040
He's definitely better than you,

399
00:46:16,840 --> 00:46:19,160
because he wouldn't invite someone
who has a boyfriend out

400
00:46:19,240 --> 00:46:21,200
for coffee alone.

401
00:46:27,520 --> 00:46:31,240
If I invite you, then you can judge me.

402
00:46:36,200 --> 00:46:37,520
What do you say?

403
00:46:40,040 --> 00:46:43,160
Thank you, but I already have plans.

404
00:46:46,520 --> 00:46:49,240
That's a shame. But it's fine.

405
00:46:50,080 --> 00:46:51,480
Next time,

406
00:46:51,560 --> 00:46:53,200
don't turn me down.

407
00:47:10,840 --> 00:47:12,120
This is for you.

408
00:47:12,200 --> 00:47:13,240
Thank you.

409
00:47:16,680 --> 00:47:20,000
Hey. What you did back there
wasn't appropriate.

410
00:47:25,560 --> 00:47:27,040
How was it inappropriate?

411
00:47:27,600 --> 00:47:29,800
Catching Ms. Maysa,

412
00:47:30,440 --> 00:47:33,240
putting her shoe back on,
or inviting her for coffee?

413
00:47:37,760 --> 00:47:41,520
Any male fan would want to do that.

414
00:47:43,520 --> 00:47:45,720
Then maybe you should learn
how to be a proper fan.

415
00:47:46,560 --> 00:47:48,800
Because what you did
looked more like stalking.

416
00:47:50,160 --> 00:47:51,120
That serious?

417
00:47:52,440 --> 00:47:54,600
Helping her counts as stalking?

418
00:47:55,280 --> 00:48:00,160
I believe someone like you is smart enough
to act more appropriately.

419
00:48:03,120 --> 00:48:04,760
You think I had other intentions?

420
00:48:08,840 --> 00:48:10,240
We can't know people's intentions.

421
00:48:11,000 --> 00:48:13,600
That's why you should be careful,

422
00:48:14,320 --> 00:48:17,800
so others don't interpret
your actions the wrong way.

423
00:48:24,640 --> 00:48:26,680
Even if you didn't mean anything,

424
00:48:27,320 --> 00:48:30,800
if people see you
getting too close to May,

425
00:48:32,000 --> 00:48:32,840
you

426
00:48:33,680 --> 00:48:37,200
might end up hurting the artist
you claim to like without even meaning to.

427
00:48:41,080 --> 00:48:41,920
Hey! Let go.

428
00:48:45,320 --> 00:48:46,840
You're being this cautious

429
00:48:47,920 --> 00:48:50,320
because you've met someone
whose intentions

430
00:48:51,240 --> 00:48:52,840
you failed to see through, right?

431
00:49:00,000 --> 00:49:03,320
Then I won't take it personally
that you misunderstood me.

432
00:49:26,800 --> 00:49:29,680
Cord, the blocking is ready. Let's go.

433
00:49:29,760 --> 00:49:31,920
I'm watching this live.

434
00:49:32,000 --> 00:49:33,400
What live?

435
00:49:33,480 --> 00:49:35,120
Mad Dog.

436
00:49:36,040 --> 00:49:37,400
- Oh, I'm listening too.
- Really?

437
00:49:40,360 --> 00:49:43,280
Our Mad Dog Gang is back to serve

438
00:49:43,360 --> 00:49:45,480
the hottest truth
everyone's been waiting for.

439
00:49:45,560 --> 00:49:46,760
As promised,

440
00:49:46,840 --> 00:49:49,960
today we're spying on a local politician

441
00:49:50,040 --> 00:49:52,200
who claims he knows nothing

442
00:49:52,280 --> 00:49:54,680
about the call-center gang
running wild everywhere.

443
00:49:55,720 --> 00:49:59,560
But before we start,
give me some hearts!

444
00:50:04,960 --> 00:50:06,520
Okay.

445
00:50:06,600 --> 00:50:09,240
With this many likes,
I'm feeling better already.

446
00:50:10,360 --> 00:50:11,840
Show it.

447
00:50:14,280 --> 00:50:18,120
<i>Those people accusing me</i>
<i>of being behind the call-center gang?</i>

448
00:50:18,200 --> 00:50:19,560
<i>I'm gonna sue them all.</i>

449
00:50:20,200 --> 00:50:23,000
<i>I'm the major partner.</i>

450
00:50:23,080 --> 00:50:24,880
<i>I run it myself, sweetheart.</i>

451
00:50:29,280 --> 00:50:31,120
You're amazing.

452
00:50:31,800 --> 00:50:33,280
How do you do it?

453
00:50:33,880 --> 00:50:36,520
<i>There's nothing much to it.</i>
<i>In this kind of business,</i>

454
00:50:36,600 --> 00:50:39,360
<i>the important thing</i>
<i>is knowing how to use people.</i>

455
00:50:39,440 --> 00:50:42,160
<i>I tell all my call-center guys this.</i>

456
00:50:42,760 --> 00:50:45,120
<i>Whether we scam them or not,</i>
<i>someone else will.</i>

457
00:50:45,720 --> 00:50:48,840
<i>If people are gonna get fooled,</i>
<i>they're gonna get fooled anyway.</i>

458
00:50:49,400 --> 00:50:51,680
<i>Money is floating everywhere.</i>

459
00:50:51,760 --> 00:50:55,320
<i>We just have to grab</i>
<i>as much of it as we can.</i>

460
00:50:55,400 --> 00:50:57,040
Damn, seriously?

461
00:50:57,120 --> 00:51:00,440
But I think I know
who that fat politician is.

462
00:51:00,520 --> 00:51:02,000
Who?

463
00:51:02,080 --> 00:51:03,840
- You wanna know?
- Yes.

464
00:51:04,400 --> 00:51:09,080
That's why I've got money
to spoil girls like you.

465
00:51:09,880 --> 00:51:13,120
If there's anything you want,
just tell me.

466
00:51:17,560 --> 00:51:19,360
Hearing that

467
00:51:20,960 --> 00:51:23,000
makes me wanna jump right in.

468
00:51:24,960 --> 00:51:26,320
Come on.

469
00:51:28,800 --> 00:51:29,640
Yeah!

470
00:51:29,720 --> 00:51:31,640
More.

471
00:51:31,720 --> 00:51:34,720
- That's it.
- That's what he deserves.

472
00:51:34,800 --> 00:51:37,440
<i>You worthless piece of trash.</i>

473
00:51:37,520 --> 00:51:39,680
<i>Bastard.</i>

474
00:51:39,760 --> 00:51:42,280
<i>You're still proud of yourself?</i>

475
00:51:44,560 --> 00:51:46,960
Thank you so much, everyone.

476
00:51:47,040 --> 00:51:48,880
Our Poodle's performance was incredible.

477
00:51:48,960 --> 00:51:51,960
Alright, Poodle, come on out.

478
00:51:52,040 --> 00:51:54,680
‪And this is Poodle. She's amazing.

479
00:51:54,760 --> 00:51:56,800
Amazing.

480
00:51:56,880 --> 00:51:58,800
But there's one more surprise.

481
00:51:58,880 --> 00:52:01,840
We also have to thank

482
00:52:01,920 --> 00:52:04,480
the one who handled security for us today,

483
00:52:04,560 --> 00:52:06,200
Rottweiler!

484
00:52:09,560 --> 00:52:11,200
I told you not to say my name.

485
00:52:11,280 --> 00:52:12,520
I told you not to say it.

486
00:52:16,440 --> 00:52:17,280
Anyway,

487
00:52:17,360 --> 00:52:20,280
another very important person for us today

488
00:52:20,360 --> 00:52:22,880
is our boss,

489
00:52:22,960 --> 00:52:25,920
the one who started this whole mission,

490
00:52:26,000 --> 00:52:29,880
Pitbull!

491
00:52:31,280 --> 00:52:33,760
The Mad Dog Gang wants to thank everyone

492
00:52:33,840 --> 00:52:37,560
for being part of today's takedown.

493
00:52:37,640 --> 00:52:39,120
Next time,

494
00:52:39,200 --> 00:52:42,400
whether it's a politician,

495
00:52:42,480 --> 00:52:46,160
a corrupt businessman,
or a crooked official,

496
00:52:46,240 --> 00:52:49,000
who will the Mad Dog Gang bite next?

497
00:52:49,080 --> 00:52:51,840
See you next time!

498
00:52:54,600 --> 00:52:56,400
Damn!

499
00:52:56,480 --> 00:52:58,240
This page is incredible, Captain.

500
00:52:58,320 --> 00:52:59,840
I seriously worship them.

501
00:53:01,000 --> 00:53:05,880
They're amazing. They can dig up
deep information like this.

502
00:53:05,960 --> 00:53:08,000
Totally next level.

503
00:53:08,080 --> 00:53:11,040
Amazing.

504
00:53:12,080 --> 00:53:13,640
You're getting too into it, Sergeant.

505
00:53:14,240 --> 00:53:17,080
We're the ones who are supposed
to expose people like this.

506
00:53:18,320 --> 00:53:20,720
How can you admire people

507
00:53:22,280 --> 00:53:24,120
who act like illegal vigilante heroes?

508
00:53:25,480 --> 00:53:29,800
Maybe they're just tools being used by
rival politicians to sabotage each other.

509
00:53:31,120 --> 00:53:33,440
When mob justice
rises above the law like this,

510
00:53:33,520 --> 00:53:36,760
who's going to know
when they start doing evil themselves?

511
00:53:56,080 --> 00:53:56,960
Yes, Dad.

512
00:53:57,040 --> 00:54:00,560
The driver told me
you took the car out yourself?

513
00:54:00,640 --> 00:54:03,120
This isn't New York, you know.

514
00:54:03,200 --> 00:54:06,480
Dad, that was six years ago.

515
00:54:07,920 --> 00:54:09,960
I know you're worried.

516
00:54:10,040 --> 00:54:13,200
But honestly, I feel safer driving myself
than letting someone else drive.

517
00:54:13,280 --> 00:54:17,240
I'm sorry Somkid did that to you.

518
00:54:17,320 --> 00:54:19,960
I trusted him to drive you around.

519
00:54:20,640 --> 00:54:22,120
Dad,

520
00:54:22,640 --> 00:54:25,240
we've talked about this enough already.

521
00:54:25,320 --> 00:54:28,280
And Uncle Somkid is gone now too.

522
00:54:30,360 --> 00:54:33,120
But I do know I have to be careful.

523
00:54:33,200 --> 00:54:34,360
I'll be there soon.

524
00:54:35,040 --> 00:54:35,920
Alright.

525
00:54:39,480 --> 00:54:42,160
The target is heading out now, bro.
Go ahead.

526
00:54:43,600 --> 00:54:47,120
Hard to believe Mr. Rakchart's daughter
goes around alone like this.

527
00:55:34,000 --> 00:55:36,080
Why are they in such a hurry?
The light's still red.

528
00:55:36,160 --> 00:55:37,360
PHRA SUMEN ROAD

529
00:55:37,440 --> 00:55:38,720
Oh?

530
00:55:39,440 --> 00:55:40,320
Why did you move?

531
00:55:40,400 --> 00:55:42,800
The guy behind us kept honking.

532
00:55:42,880 --> 00:55:44,920
But we're tailing her.

533
00:55:45,000 --> 00:55:46,560
She'll drive past anyway,

534
00:55:46,640 --> 00:55:48,880
then we just follow again. That's it.

535
00:56:08,640 --> 00:56:09,680
Oh?

536
00:56:10,400 --> 00:56:11,240
She turned.

537
00:56:12,360 --> 00:56:13,200
Oh?

538
00:56:13,720 --> 00:56:15,320
So what do we do now?

539
00:56:40,960 --> 00:56:44,360
I've wanted to develop
that area for a long time.

540
00:56:45,200 --> 00:56:48,360
Your industrial city project
is quite interesting.

541
00:56:49,480 --> 00:56:51,840
I'll need some time to consider it.

542
00:56:51,920 --> 00:56:54,880
Of course. I'm already grateful
you're considering it.

543
00:56:57,040 --> 00:56:58,080
Well…

544
00:56:59,480 --> 00:57:01,040
My daughter should be here by now.

545
00:57:21,840 --> 00:57:25,400
Hey. All you have to do

546
00:57:26,000 --> 00:57:28,960
is plug this into the main computer
in the control room.

547
00:57:29,560 --> 00:57:32,000
That's it. You can do it, right?

548
00:57:52,840 --> 00:57:55,440
Siberian, in position.
Bangkaew, do you copy?

549
00:58:02,440 --> 00:58:04,960
Bangkaew? Bangkaew?

550
00:58:05,560 --> 00:58:06,960
Yeah, I hear you.

551
00:58:15,080 --> 00:58:16,280
What about Rottweiler?

552
00:58:18,800 --> 00:58:19,760
Good afternoon, miss.

553
00:58:20,280 --> 00:58:21,240
Your father asked me to escort you.

554
00:58:21,320 --> 00:58:22,800
- Alright.
- This way, please.

555
00:58:30,240 --> 00:58:31,600
Excuse me. Are you security?

556
00:58:32,360 --> 00:58:33,880
Someone fell off a motorcycle outside.

557
00:58:33,960 --> 00:58:35,040
Can you help?

558
00:58:35,120 --> 00:58:36,960
I'm not security.

559
00:58:38,440 --> 00:58:39,640
Please go help them.

560
00:58:44,720 --> 00:58:47,240
- Yes, miss.
- This way.

561
00:58:49,360 --> 00:58:50,440
You shouldn't come.

562
00:58:50,520 --> 00:58:52,240
It'll just scare you.

563
00:58:54,080 --> 00:58:55,760
Then who's going with the target?

564
00:58:56,960 --> 00:58:57,880
Let's go.

565
00:59:03,320 --> 00:59:04,160
Pitbull ready.

566
00:59:05,720 --> 00:59:07,200
That's why you're the boss.

567
00:59:15,600 --> 00:59:16,760
Which floor?

568
00:59:19,000 --> 00:59:20,280
You…

569
00:59:20,880 --> 00:59:22,720
If you can't decide,
just come to my floor.

570
00:59:34,040 --> 00:59:37,120
Pitbull is in the elevator.
Bangkaew, you've got 45 seconds.

571
00:59:41,080 --> 00:59:42,480
Hey, who are you?

572
00:59:42,560 --> 00:59:44,960
I'm new, sir.

573
00:59:45,040 --> 00:59:47,240
I brought you some coffee.

574
00:59:47,320 --> 00:59:49,240
Nice to meet you. Here it is.

575
00:59:50,240 --> 00:59:51,080
Ah! It's hot!

576
00:59:51,160 --> 00:59:53,000
I'm so sorry.

577
00:59:53,080 --> 00:59:55,040
I didn't mean to.

578
00:59:56,040 --> 00:59:57,640
- What the hell?
- I'm sorry.

579
00:59:57,720 --> 01:00:00,040
Maybe go wash up?

580
01:00:00,120 --> 01:00:01,720
I'll watch this for you.

581
01:00:01,800 --> 01:00:02,920
You weren't careful at all!

582
01:00:03,000 --> 01:00:04,480
I'm sorry.

583
01:00:10,240 --> 01:00:11,400
DON'T SET THE AIR CONDITIONER
BELOW 24 DEGREES

584
01:00:23,080 --> 01:00:24,520
Here we go.

585
01:00:29,480 --> 01:00:30,760
Great.

586
01:00:30,840 --> 01:00:33,200
From now on,
I control everything from here.

587
01:00:36,160 --> 01:00:37,400
Let's begin with…

588
01:00:48,480 --> 01:00:49,320
Phone unlocked.

589
01:00:49,920 --> 01:00:51,080
I've got this.

590
01:00:53,680 --> 01:00:55,120
You'll be safe.

591
01:01:03,240 --> 01:01:05,000
<i>Hello, Ms. Fahsai.</i>

592
01:01:06,920 --> 01:01:10,720
<i>Has no one ever told you</i>
<i>that at the place you're standing…</i>

593
01:01:10,800 --> 01:01:12,000
<i>…someone died right there?</i>

594
01:01:13,000 --> 01:01:16,320
- Is this really his house?
- Huh?

595
01:01:16,400 --> 01:01:18,120
I want to know the truth.

596
01:01:18,200 --> 01:01:21,160
Captain. Someone transported
a suspect with a gunshot wound

597
01:01:21,240 --> 01:01:22,320
into a restricted area.

598
01:01:22,400 --> 01:01:24,680
This time, those Black Dogs
won't get away.

599
01:01:24,760 --> 01:01:25,800
They're down there.

600
01:01:30,400 --> 01:01:32,240
Permission to search.

601
01:01:33,320 --> 01:01:34,520
Go ahead.

602
01:02:39,480 --> 01:02:41,400
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
